title: For Sale:  Thermal-Eye Renegade 320 Thermal Imaging Handheld/Weapon Sight
location: Cary, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent: If you want to avoid paying too much, this is a great deal on a used Thermal Imager. There is a minor chip on the housing, but the unit still works perfectly. With a Renegade thermal scope, you have the advantage. You can see targets long before they see you. The scope does not rely on light, as it uses infrared heat energy. This means that in can be used in complete darkness, or broad daylight. Thermal imaging technology allows you to detect living things that would not be seen otherwise. title: For Sale:  AR-15 300 Blackout 10.5" pistol
postcontent:
I got excited and bought too many ARs because I thought I was going to get paid for some work but now it looks like I won't get paid, so I have to sell them. This one is one of my favorites. The 300 blackout chambering offers superior ballistics in a compact package, making for a great trunk gun, backpacking gun, home defense, etc. Basically, it hits like an AK but pops more like a 9mm, which is why these guns run great supressed. Blackout ammo prices keep falling (found some for about 40 cents/round the other day) and people are saying that the 5.56 may go the way of the dinosaur. I doubt that, but still, this is a fantastic chambering to have in your AR. One of the best things about it is that the only difference is the barrel, so if you do just a simple, easy, quick barrel swap (it takes about 15-20 min with an armorers wrench) you can go back and forth between 300 blackout and 5.56/.223. The magazines, the bolt, everything else is the same. It shoots very nice and is easy to become proficient at, especially with the single point sling. I've dropped the price to the rock bottom so this is priced to sell and I don't expect it to last long. Comes with a magazine and 30 rds of ammo and there's more I can sell you if you want. You can't buy or build an AR this nice for this price anywhere.
